subject: Re: Quality with a K
msgSnippet: Certainly, if you re spelling Unique . {yunik} The word Quick has four separate sounds, kwik . The original Q gave you no more information about the
messageBody:
Certainly, if you're spelling 'Unique'. {yunik}

   The word 'Quick' has four separate sounds, 'kwik'. The original 'Q' gave you no more information about the sound than 'k' does, the original 'u' gives no more information that 'w', and original 'ck' is easily represented by 'k'. (i is i.)
   If you skip the 'u' or 'w' when writing the word, your reader will see a different word: 'Kick'.
Quick and Kick in QuikScript (Thoth font)


   That said, the main purpose most have for QS is as a personal shorthand. It would be easy to decide that a certain 'tick' from the bottom of the 'k' character would mean a 'w' follows. If you made it a straight diagonal resembling the top half of the 'w' character, it should even be understandable by other QS users - though recognized as a non-standard usage.
